AU  - Spatt, Chester S
AU  - Ye, Mao
T1  - The Next Chapter of Big Data in Finance
PY  - 2025
Y1  - 2025/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhae083
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 38
IS  - 3
SP  - 605
EP  - 622
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - The second special issue on big data in finance showcases advancements in research related to data of large size, high dimension, and complex structure since the first NBER/RFS big data conference. The papers published in this next chapter address some questions that were proposed in the initial special issue in 2021. Other papers are more directly connected to recent developments in the markets. We discuss some new research directions, following on the papers published here. They include evaluating market microstructure reforms, understanding medium-frequency trading, improving missing data imputations, and deepening data valuation. We look forward to more developments to follow.
Y2  - 5/12/2025
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhae083
ER  - 



