TY  - JOUR
AU  - Freyberger, Joachim
AU  - Hoeppner, Bjoern
AU  - Neuhierl, Andreas
AU  - Weber, Michael
T1  - Missing Data in Asset Pricing Panels
PY  - 2025
Y1  - 2025/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhae003
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 38
IS  - 3
SP  - 760
EP  - 802
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We propose a simple and computationally attractive method to deal with missing data in in cross-sectional asset pricing using conditional mean imputations and weighted least squares, cast in a generalized method of moments (GMM) framework. This method allows us to use all observations with observed returns; it results in valid inference; and it can be applied in nonlinear and high-dimensional settings. In simulations, we find it performs almost as well as the efficient but computationally costly GMM estimator. We apply our procedure to a large panel of return predictors and find that it leads to improved out-of-sample predictability.
Y2  - 5/12/2025
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhae003
ER  - 



